{
  "text": "The Leydigioma is a rare tumor of the testicle. It develops from the proliferation of the interstitial cells or Leydig cells, and compete with the endocrine activity of this organ. [CITATION_1] It usually arises between 20 year and 50 year of life, and rarely reported in children. [CITATION_2] International literature is rich about the management of testicular tumors in adults and often recommends radical orchidectomy. Few reports of pediatric Leydig cells tumors exist in literature. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The tumor cells produce androgen hormones and manifests with precocious physical and sexual development. [CITATION_5] Rarely the tumor is asymptomatic. We report a case of asymptomatic Leydig cell tumor managed by testis sparing surgery.",
